-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
NOTICE — Rationale for Licensing Choice
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Legacy Ag Limited has chosen the MIT License for the cultivation-intelligence
platform for the following reasons:

1. Operator Ownership and Freedom
   As an agricultural operator, Legacy Ag Limited must retain full sovereignty
   over the software that controls its cultivation environment. The MIT License
   ensures no vendor lock-in: the company may modify, redeploy, sublicense, or
   hand the software to a third-party contractor at any time without seeking
   permission or paying royalties.

2. Collaboration with New Zealand Agtech Partners
   The NZ agtech ecosystem is small and collaborative. A permissive licence
   removes legal friction when sharing sensor-integration code, agronomic
   feature-engineering libraries, or cultivation model artefacts with research
   institutions, crop-science consultants, or fellow licensed cultivators. It
   also enables code contributions back to the community without encumbering
   contributors with copyleft obligations.

3. Alignment with Open-Source Stack
   The platform is built entirely on MIT/Apache-2.0-licensed open-source
   tooling — FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Alembic, scikit-learn, LightGBM, Pydantic,
   Structlog, and TimescaleDB. Adopting the MIT License ensures licence
   compatibility across the full dependency tree and avoids licence conflicts
   when bundling or distributing the platform as part of a larger solution.

4. Regulatory Transparency
   New Zealand's Misuse of Drugs (Medicinal Cannabis) Regulations 2019 require
   licensed cultivators to maintain detailed records and allow Ministry of
   Health audits. An open licence facilitates independent code review by
   auditors and regulators without requiring separate non-disclosure agreements,
   supporting Legacy Ag's compliance obligations.
